            <p:rationale>The portal environment is often the face of the organization to customers, employees and external partners. Organizations have an increased expectation for 24x7 accessibility of the portal environment. It is vital to make the system highly available such that users can reach the organization at all times, regardless of back-office systems availability.</p:rationale>
            <p:implications>There are no inherent limitations in the design of the portal environment to limit availability. The portal environment is redundant, and preferably the portal environment is used as a service. Back-office systems need not be as highly available. Available by definition 24x7, the portal environment provides users facilities to submit requests to back-office systems, which can handle those requests at a later time.</p:implications>
